## 6. Engineering Rules

### Mandatory architecture (do not change without ADR)

| Principle | Rule |
|-----------|------|
| ECU | Engine only — injection, ignition, boost, protection, telemetry |
| DCC | Vehicle — PDM, VCM, loads, diagnostics, logging, config execution |
| STM32 | Real-time and safety-relevant control; works without ESP32/tablet |
| ESP32 | Service layer — Wi-Fi, REST, WebSocket, OTA, UI assets |
| Tablet | Presentation client only; not required for operation |
| Config | Logical functions → physical channels via YAML; not in firmware |
| CAN Gen1 | One CAN FD bus, linear: DCC — ECU — Button Box |
| SPI | Binary DCPI STM32↔ESP32; JSON only for browser clients |

### Decision discipline

- Minimal scope per task; no unrelated refactor.
- No speculative “future-proof” features without approved requirement.
- Do not create architecture by implication (extra CAN bus, ESP32 safety, tablet mandatory, etc.).
- Mark unknowns explicitly.

### Prohibited actions

- Invent datasheet values or infer current from part numbers.
- Approve own architecture changes.
- Claim unrun tests as passed.
- Continue past assigned task without new authorization.

Refs: `docs/001`, `docs/003`, `docs/006`, `docs/EDL/`.

