## 11. Escalation Policy

Implementation **must stop** when any of the following occurs:

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| Architecture conflict | STOP → ARCHITECTURAL DECISION REQUIRED |
| Missing requirements | STOP → report open questions |
| Component selection required | STOP → qualification WP or architect |
| Safety decision required | STOP → architect + SRS |
| Protocol redesign | STOP → ADR required |
| Conflicting documentation | STOP → report; do not silently pick one |
| Missing interface definition | STOP → interface WP |
| Insufficient engineering evidence | STOP → measurement or qualification |
| Undefined ownership | STOP → architect assigns module owner |

### ARCHITECTURAL DECISION REQUIRED report

Include: context, conflict, options considered (if any), impact, recommended architect action, work blocked until resolved.

