## 18. Review Process

**Every change requires review.**

### Mandatory internal review sequence

| Stage | Purpose | Mindset |
|-------|---------|---------|
| **1. Implementation Review** | Self-check: scope, diff, validation honesty | Confirm task completion |
| **2. Engineering Review** | Peer/architect check: requirements, traceability, docs | Confirm engineering quality |
| **3. Critical Review** | Actively search for weaknesses — **not** confirm success | Challenge assumptions, find gaps |

### Review checklist

| Area | Verify |
|------|--------|
| Requirements | Diff matches stated task scope only |
| Architecture | No ADR-level change without approval |
| Tests | Executed tests reported honestly; unrun = NOT VERIFIED |
| Documentation | Affected docs updated; constitution hierarchy respected |
| Risks | Assumptions, regressions, open questions listed |

### Document statuses (authorized use only)

Concept · Proposed · Under Review · Approved for DevKit · Approved for Prototype · Verified · Deprecated

Do not mark Approved or Verified without explicit instruction.

### Outcomes

Accepted · Revision required · Blocked (architectural decision needed)

Extended: `docs/REVIEW_PROCESS.md`, `docs/templates/Architecture_Review_Template.md`.

