## 19. Definition of Done

A task is complete **only if:**

| Criterion | Required |
|-----------|----------|
| Documentation updated | Affected docs reflect changes |
| Traceability preserved | Requirement IDs, WP/CR references intact |
| Cross-references verified | Links resolve; pointers consistent |
| No duplicated information | Policy not copied outside constitution |
| No unresolved contradictions | Conflicts escalated, not hidden |
| Architecture preserved | No unauthorized ADR-level changes |
| Validation completed | Honest report — NOT VERIFIED where applicable |
| Completion report generated | All mandatory sections present |
| No unauthorized engineering decisions | Escalations documented |

Then: **Stop.** Wait for review. No further work without new task.

---

## 20. Mandatory Completion Report

At task end, provide:

1. Task Summary  
2. Files Created  
3. Files Modified  
4. Validation Performed  
5. Acceptance Criteria (PASS / FAIL / PARTIAL / NOT VERIFIED)  
6. Open Questions  
7. Risks and Observations (or Architectural Decisions Required)  
8. Out-of-Scope Recommendations (or Improvement Suggestions — do not implement)  
9. Final Status: Ready for Review · Blocked · Partially Complete · Failed Validation  

Work packages may specify additional sections (e.g. Architect Review Package for WP-006).

Template: `docs/templates/Work_Package_Template.md`.

